# Icons: Lucide only — no emoji

Do **not** use emoji or emoticon characters (e.g. 🖨️, ⬇, 📄, ✅) as UI icons, button prefixes, or navigation affordances.

Use **`lucide-react`** icons instead, consistent with the rest of this codebase.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<Button>⬇ ดาวน์โหลด</Button>
<a href="/back">← กลับ</a>

// ✅ GOOD
import { Download, ArrowLeft } from "lucide-react";

<Button className="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
  <Download className="size-4" aria-hidden />
  ดาวน์โหลด
</Button>
<Link href="/back" className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5">
  <ArrowLeft className="size-3.5" aria-hidden />
  กลับ
</Link>
```

## Accessibility

- Decorative icons: `aria-hidden` on the SVG.
- Icon-only controls: add `aria-label` on the button/link.

## Exceptions

- **Printed / exported documents** (PDF, Excel, official summary sheets) may use plain text marks required by the format (e.g. `✓` in a judges grid cell) when they are data notation, not decorative UI chrome.
